name: pytest-socket
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pytest-socket" %}
{% set version = "0.5.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7c4b81dc6a51cbc0093f11791de00ff4a15ac698f5da96879a80f5d9ad4179b6

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - poetry-core >=1.0.0
    - python >=3.7
  run:
    - pytest >=3.6.3
    - python >=3.7

test:
  requires:
    - pip
  imports:
    - pytest_socket
  commands:
    - python -m pip check

about:
  home: https://github.com/miketheman/pytest-socket
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Pytest Plugin to disable socket calls during tests
  description: |
    A plugin to use with Pytest to disable or restrict socket calls
    during tests to ensure network calls are prevented.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - duncanmmacleod
